# Azure RTOS (ThreadX) stack map: name  stack_size  peak_used  [priority]
# Automotive body-control module on an NXP S32K. peak_used recovered by
# walking each thread's stack for the 0xEFEFEFEF fill pattern (ThreadX
# pre-fills stacks, so the lowest untouched fill word marks the high water).
# ThreadX priorities: 0 = highest.
system_timer   1024   360    0
canopen_rx     2048   1880   3
canopen_tx     2048   1120   3
lin_master     1536   980    5
diag_uds       3072   2960   6
door_ctrl      1024   560    8
light_ctrl     1024   600    8
nvm_writeback  2048   1340   10
